SCHOOL MANAGEMENT SYSTEM BACKEND

To start backend :
    cd backend
    npm start

USED FILES AND FOLDERS

server.js
config
model
controllers
router
middleware
service
.env
.gitignore
nodemodules
package.json
README

config            - db.js - connecting to mongoDB database

model            - User.js
                 - student.js
                 - FeesRecord.js
                 - LibraryRecord.js 

controllers      - authController.js
                 - studentController.js
                 - feesController.js
                 - libraryController.js 

router           - auth.js
                 - student.js
                 - fees.js
                 - library.js

middleware       - authMiddleware.js  -middleware function verifies the provided JWT token from the authorization header, decodes the user data, and allows access to protected routes if the token is valid. 

service          - sendToken.js -This function generates an access token for a user, logs it for debugging, and sends the token along with user details as a JSON response.

.env           PORT = 8000
               MONGODB=mongodb://localhost:27017/schoolmanagement
               MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://anushma007:school@cluster0.apbdi.mongodb.net/school
               TOKEN_SECRET = schooltokensecret123

